                        Yes. You can change your company name at any time post-incorporation by submitting a Special Resolution to Companies House. Once the government approves the request, they will issue a formal Certificate of Name Change, and all statutory registers will be updated automatically.
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- FAQ 3 -->
